@@ -0,0 +1,18 @@
+# ADR 0002 — Shared structure, separate public and private planes
+
+**Status:** Accepted for v2 prototype
+
+## Decision
+
+Public authority records and private enterprise work may reference the same source and rule identities, but must use separate authorization, storage, retrieval, and caching boundaries.
+
+## Rationale
+
+The public authority layer creates trust and discoverability. The enterprise layer may contain privileged analysis and sensitive workforce data. “Unified” must not mean commingled access.
+
+## Consequences
+
+- explicit context and permission checks
+- tenant-aware retrieval and AI assembly
+- no implicit private context in public search
+- public content remains reusable without exposing derived tenant records
