@@ -0,0 +1,18 @@
+# ADR 0003 — Separate deterministic logic from counsel judgment
+
+**Status:** Accepted for v2 prototype
+
+## Decision
+
+Store and present rule application, arithmetic, assumptions, legal interpretation, and recommendation as distinct layers.
+
+## Rationale
+
+Opaque outputs are difficult to verify and dangerous to operationalize. Many wage-and-hour questions combine computable rules with factual uncertainty and legal judgment.
+
+## Consequences
+
+- tool outputs require branch traces and model versions
+- “confidence” cannot substitute for disclosed dimensions
+- counsel can override or qualify outputs without mutating the underlying computation
+- tests can validate deterministic logic independently
