+# Product analytics and operating measures
+
+## Measurement principle
+
+The platform should optimize the quality and speed of legal response—not page views, search volume, or the number of generated summaries.
+
+Analytics must never become a shadow copy of privileged facts or legal work product. Event payloads should use durable record IDs, categorical states, and timing metadata; sensitive text belongs in the system of record, not the analytics pipeline.
+
+## North-star outcome
+
+**Material change response integrity**: the percentage of material legal changes that reach a complete, approved, and current response record before the applicable deadline.
+
+A complete response has:
+
+- verified authority
+- resolved or explicitly open applicability facts
+- approved findings
+- accountable actions
+- linked controls and evidence expectations
+- a decision record when leadership judgment is required
+- no unacknowledged invalidation state
+
+## Primary operating measures
+
+| Measure | Definition | Why it matters |
+|---|---|---|
+| Change-to-triage time | detection to accepted materiality review | monitors signal latency |
+| Triage-to-scope time | accepted change to portfolio reach decision | measures fact and applicability readiness |
+| Scope-to-decision time | scope confirmation to approved decision | measures legal-operating throughput |
+| Decision-to-control time | approval to implemented control state | prevents “approved but not operational” work |
+| Evidence currency | controls with current accepted evidence / controls requiring evidence | measures provability |
+| Revalidation latency | invalidating event to reviewed dependent records | measures system integrity after change |
+| Open material fact gaps | unresolved applicability facts on material matters | exposes hidden uncertainty |
+| Source lineage coverage | approved propositions with passage-level primary authority | measures defensibility |
+| Rework rate | findings or decisions reopened due to missing facts or lineage defects | diagnoses process quality |
+| Deadline reliability | required actions completed by governed due date | measures execution |
+
+## Executive measures
+
+Executives should see a small number of denominator-disclosing measures:
+
+- material decisions due in the next 30 days
+- properties with unresolved high-impact applicability
+- controls with material exceptions
+- approved decisions awaiting implementation proof
+- invalidated records awaiting review
+- changes with no accountable matter owner
+
+A red count without scope, age, materiality, and owner is not an executive metric.
+
+## Product-behavior events
+
+Representative events:
+
+```text
+change.opened
+change.scope_review_started
+change.converted_to_matter
+matter.fact_requested
+matter.finding_submitted
+matter.finding_approved
+scenario.executed
+control.opened
+control.evidence_requested
+control.exception_opened
+research.answer_viewed
+research.answer_saved_to_matter
+decision.submitted
+decision.approved
+decision.invalidated
+source.chain_opened
+```
+
+Each event should include:
+
+- event ID and UTC timestamp
+- tenant ID and pseudonymous actor ID
+- record type and record ID
+- workflow state before and after
+- interface surface
+- latency or duration where relevant
+- result category
+- schema version
+
+It should not include:
+
+- query text by default
+- legal analysis prose
+- evidence contents
+- employee names or payroll values
+- privilege-bearing matter descriptions
+- source excerpts beyond categorical metadata
+
+## Quality telemetry
+
+Legal and model quality require operational telemetry beyond product usage:
+
+- citation resolution success
+- source retrieval and freshness failures
+- source diff false-positive rate
+- rule-fixture pass rate
+- applicability branch coverage
+- deterministic replay success
+- model version drift
+- attorney override frequency and rationale category
+- search answer citation sufficiency
+- unauthorized retrieval attempts
+
+## Experimentation limits
+
+Do not A/B test legal conclusions, warning severity, evidence requirements, or approval standards. Experiments may address navigation, terminology, layout, and workflow efficiency only when they preserve the same governed outcome and are reviewed for bias and privilege leakage.
+
+## Analytics access
+
+- access is role-restricted and audited
+- tenant aggregates require minimum cohort sizes
+- record-level analytics links return the user to the authorized system of record
+- analytics retention is shorter than legal-system retention unless separately justified
+- deletion and legal-hold behavior are documented
